Good morning Sean,

We have a customer that has Canada General Warranty, his 2019 Skidoo MXZ XRS 850 came in with the engine only running on one cylinder. We thought it was potentially a fouled spark plug but when we removed the spark plugs to inspect we found aluminum debris on the PTO spark plug. We remove the exhaust to inspect the piston condition and can see some damage to the piston. We then performed a compression test and found the PTO cylinder to read 60 psi and the Mag cylinder at 115 psi. A good running engine should be around 125 psi on the 850 etec engines. At this point there is no easy way out of this, these engines are very advanced and once a piston lets go, there is debris that makes its way into the crankshaft and will cause crankshaft failure. We need a complete short block engine to repair this properly. We priced out the OEM engine and again it is much pricier, we do have an option from CV-Tech for a short block which is the much more affordable route.
